    </div>

    <!-- Slide 3: Answer -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-3">
      <div class="difficulty">10-Year-Old Difficulty</div>
      <p class="answer">California Trout</p>
      <p class="note">Working to ensure resilient wild fish in healthy waters</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 4: Question -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-4">
      <div class="difficulty">Super High-Level Difficulty</div>
      <p class="question">What is the difference between anadromous steelhead and resident rainbow trout?</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 5: Answer -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-5">
      <div class="difficulty">Super High-Level Difficulty</div>
      <p class="answer">Anadromous steelhead migrate to sea, whereas resident rainbow trout spend their entire life in fresh water</p>
      <p class="note">Same species, different life strategies</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 6: Question -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-6">
      <div class="difficulty">Average Difficulty</div>
      <p class="question">In what year was California Trout founded?</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 7: Answer -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-7">
      <div class="difficulty">Average Difficulty</div>
      <p class="answer">1971</p>
      <p class="note">Over 50 years of conservation work in California</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 8: Question -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-8">
      <div class="difficulty">10-Year-Old Difficulty</div>
      <p class="question">What type of fish is the California state fish?</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 9: Answer -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-9">
      <div class="difficulty">10-Year-Old Difficulty</div>
      <p class="answer">California Golden Trout</p>
      <p class="note">A beautiful native species found in high mountain streams</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 10: Question -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-10">
      <div class="difficulty">Super High-Level Difficulty</div>
      <p class="question">What is the public trust doctrine?</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 11: Answer -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-11">
      <div class="difficulty">Super High-Level Difficulty</div>
      <p class="answer">A principle that natural resources are held in trust for the benefit of all people and the state has an obligation to protect them</p>
      <p class="note">The legal foundation for many environmental protections</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 12: Question -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-12">
      <div class="difficulty">Average Difficulty</div>
      <p class="question">What is the main threat affecting salmonid populations in California?</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 13: Answer -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-13">
      <div class="difficulty">Average Difficulty</div>
      <p class="answer">Climate change</p>
      <p class="note">Warming waters and changing precipitation patterns are threatening native fish</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 14: Question -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-14">
      <div class="difficulty">10-Year-Old Difficulty</div>
      <p class="question">What is a "catch and release" approach to fishing?</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 15: Answer -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-15">
      <div class="difficulty">10-Year-Old Difficulty</div>
      <p class="answer">Returning fish to the water after catching them</p>
      <p class="note">A conservation practice that helps maintain fish populations</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 16: Question -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-16">
      <div class="difficulty">Super High-Level Difficulty</div>
      <p class="question">What are the challenges in using hatchery fish for restoration efforts?</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 17: Answer -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-17">
      <div class="difficulty">Super High-Level Difficulty</div>
      <p class="answer">Hatchery fish can have genetic and ecological impacts on wild populations</p>
      <p class="note">Including straying, competition, and hybridization with wild fish</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 18: Question -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-18">
      <div class="difficulty">Average Difficulty</div>
      <p class="question">What percentage of California salmonids could be extinct in the next 50 years if current trends continue?</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 19: Answer -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-19">
      <div class="difficulty">Average Difficulty</div>
      <p class="answer">45%</p>
      <p class="note">According to the State of the Salmonids report, nearly half of native salmonids face extinction</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 20: Question -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-20">
      <div class="difficulty">10-Year-Old Difficulty</div>
      <p class="question">What is one thing that dams do that's bad for fish?</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 21: Answer -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-21">
      <div class="difficulty">10-Year-Old Difficulty</div>
      <p class="answer">Block fish from swimming to their spawning grounds</p>
      <p class="note">Creating barriers in migration routes essential for reproduction</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 22: Question -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-22">
      <div class="difficulty">Species-Specific High Difficulty</div>
      <p class="question">What makes the Klamath Mountains Province summer steelhead particularly vulnerable?</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 23: Answer -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-23">
      <div class="difficulty">Species-Specific High Difficulty</div>
      <p class="answer">Their reliance on cold water sources during the warmest summer months</p>
      <p class="note">These cold water refuges are becoming increasingly rare due to climate change</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 24: Question -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-24">
      <div class="difficulty">Average Difficulty</div>
      <p class="question">What are the three conservation initiatives that California Trout focuses on?</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 25: Answer -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-25">
      <div class="difficulty">Average Difficulty</div>
      <p class="answer">Strongholds, Source Water Areas, and Wild Fish, Working Landscapes</p>
      <p class="note">Strategic priorities that guide CalTrout's conservation efforts</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 26: Question -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-26">
      <div class="difficulty">10-Year-Old Difficulty</div>
      <p class="question">True or False: Healthy fish mean healthy waters.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 27: Answer -->
    <div class="slide" id="slide-27">
      <div class="difficulty">10-Year-Old Difficulty</div>
      <p class="answer">TRUE</p>
      <p class="note">The health of fish populations directly reflects the health of our waterways</p>
    </div>

